----------Create a Linux Environment for your project-----------------

- Install Virtual environment package 
 
python3 -m pip install --user virtualenv

- Create a Virtual Environement (folder)

python3 -m virtualenv env 

#env is the name of your virtual environment... it can be any name of choice 

- Activate the Virtual Environment created 

source env/bin/activate

- Install Jupyter Notebook

pip3 install jupyterlab
pip3 install notebook

- create a Jupyter notebook Kernel to make the virtual Environment available in Jupyter Notebook 

python3 -m ipykernel install --user --name=env

- Launch Jupyter Notebook workspace

jupyter notebook


#Please note for recent versions of jupyter notebook, an empty page might load up with http://localhost:8888/tree error
When this happens rather than use *jupyter notebook* to launch your workspace use *Jupyter lab*
